cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on deep learning for visual recognition, specifically on unsupervised domain adaptation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel architecture for domain adaptation, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of multimodal benchmark datasets suggests that the paper may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of different deep learning architectures, which falls under the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
